Protocol on technical cooperation and mutual assistance in the field of civil defence. Signed at Evora on 9 March 1992.

For the purposes of this protocol, scientific and technical cooperation be tween the two countries may include the following:

The joint preparation and implementation of specific programmes and projects;

The dispatch of technicians to provide advisory and consulting services;

The acceptance of scholarship students at the institutions of either party for the purpose of occupational and technical training;

The planning and implementation of joint activities;

The organization of conferences, meetings, courses and seminars;

The exchange of information, documentation, publications and teaching materials;

Any other type of scientific or technical cooperation agreed upon by the parties

